{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a2cb7083-760f-4c20-8c0e-140e4c0d4524","content":"In **.NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default** — no opt-in needed. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was the .NET 9 opt-in flag and is now obsolete. You can safely remove it.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01UKvTMvXSvhKju1ah5BUUwY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01UB8kL9jKXvkGmfJAy77s51","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ccef8b30f15942a28ecc6ef0a2f20a0b/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ccef8b30f15942a28ecc6ef0a2f20a0b/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"639b5cdb-847e-43e6-98c6-530ef045529b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about MTP support. Let me provide the key information:\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has native Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) support built-in. The property `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` was needed in .NET 9 to opt into the MTP-based `dotnet test` experience, but in .NET 10 it's the default behavior, so that property is no longer needed.\n\nLet me update their project file.","outputTokens":393,"requestId":"1BC3:19BA48:1F6A8E0:22D6EDD:6A03CF19"},"id":"115b4842-1614-4051-afa2-aec67c4b496c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:08:48.575Z","parentId":"8930e356-ff35-4050-ba15-42428059fd03"}
